metadata.name: 7VV1N5 #667
metadata.description:
GO BIG OR GO HOME.

After a week of minimalism code, our hero, the handsome artist Daniel, decided he needed something involving maximalism to reset the balance. Finding pairs to put together is satisfying.

Images will take 6-9 seconds to display and refresh between window resizing.

Use the z key or single click/tap to switch to "zoom" mode, which zooms in and fills the viewport; use z & tap/click to cycle through views. Use x and double-click/tap to go back to square mode.

Note: It doesn't work on Internet Explorer, because Microsoft. iOS is faster than Android.

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

z, click, tap - Switch to & cycle "zoom" mode
x, double-click, double-tap - Switch back out of "zoom" mode.
h - Toggle high-res (slow)
s - Download and save image (takes a few seconds, longer for high-res)

metadata.name: 70s Tapestry #2
metadata.description:
70s Tapestry is a tribute to the fine art work of embroiderers, and the 70s design.

Variations include :

- 10 Color Palettes
- Dark or Light background
- A reversed color mode
- 1 or 2 palettes used
- 4 types of framing, including a randomized one
- 3 types of embroidery tile type distribution
- and some special rare traits

metadata.name: Hello World #71
metadata.description:
With this token, I am entering a new chapter in making generative art. 

I recorded myself saying "Hello World" and converted the sound file to a set of amplitudes extracted from my voice. That set of amplitudes was then used to create a rotating set of discs that are orbiting a "Sun". 

As the system is rotating, the details of a generative overlay can be seen more clearly. This overlay is also a sneak peak into my next artwork coming soon.

Press keys 1-4 to change the view, press "F" to toggle framerate between 60 and 30.

metadata.name: Klimtiche #1
metadata.description:
Inspired by the 'Tree of Life' by Gustav Klimt.
Every bird comes with a default weather setting but all weather is optional.
On the keyboard:
use 's' to make it snow
use 'w' to make wind blow
use 'r' to make it rain
use 'n' to stop the animation and then again to clear all animation. 
Variables are snow intensity, rain intensity, wind speed and palette.
Made in p5.js, every tree / meadow / sky is unique in design.
Two birds is rare.
Monochrome is rare.
